Paper: hep-th/0210172

Date: 2002-10-17

Title: Axions

Authors: Mark Srednicki

Comments: 12 pages

I give a pedagogical and historical introduction to axion physics, andbriefly review the present status of axions in our understanding of particlephysics and cosmology. This is a contribution to Continuous Advances in QCD2002/Arkadyfest, held in honor of Arkady Vainshtein's 60th birthday.